revision.text: {{also|yellowman}} ==English== ===Proper noun=== {{en-prop|s}} # {{surname|en}}. ===Statistics=== * According to the 2010 United States Census, ''Yellowman'' is the 64,200<sup>th</sup> most common surname in the United States, belonging to 310 individuals. ''Yellowman'' is most common among American Indian/Alaska Native (98.06%) individuals.
